MOGALE CITY - Patrick Lipudi's stay as the ANC mayor of Mogale City could be short-lived.That s if opposition parties have their way.Lipudi, who was the council speaker, was elected to the position in a secret vote on Wednesday.READ: Mogale City elects new mayor through secret ballotHe received 39 votes and Michael Holenstein, the DA's former mayor, garnered 36.Two votes were spoilt.The opposition says his appointment cannot go unchallenged, as he presided over his own election.The ANC has described the opposition's cries as sour grapes.eNCA